Sure, I can help you create a basic sales HTML website. Here are the steps you can follow:

1. Choose a text editor: You can use any text editor to write your HTML code such as Notepad, Sublime Text, Visual Studio Code, etc. 

2. Start with a HTML document: Create a new file and start with the HTML boilerplate code. 

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Sales HTML Site</title>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>Welcome to our Sales Site!</h1>
</body>
</html>
```

3. Add content: Now you can add content to your website. Add titles, images, descriptions, etc. in a structured format.

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Sales HTML Site</title>
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<h1>Welcome to our Sales Site!</h1>
		<nav>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="#products">Products</a></li>
				<li><a href="#about">About us</a></li>
				<li><a href="#contact">Contact us</a></li>
			</ul>
		</nav>
	</header>
	<main>
		<section id="products">
			<h2>Our Products</h2>
			<img src="product1.jpg" alt="Product 1">
			<h3>Product 1</h3>
			<p>Description of product 1.</p>

			<img src="product2.jpg" alt="Product 2">
			<h3>Product 2</h3>
			<p>Description of product 2.</p>
		</section>
		<section id="about">
			<h2>About us</h2>
			<p>We are a sales company that provides quality products to our customers.</p>
		</section>
		<section id="contact">
			<h2>Contact us</h2>
			<p>Fill out the form below to contact us:</p>
			<form>
				<label for="name">Name:</label>
				<input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
				<label for="email">Email:</label>
				<input type="email" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
				<label for="message">Message:</label><br>
				<textarea id="message" name="message" rows="5" cols="30"></textarea><br><br>
				<input type="submit" value="Submit">
			</form>
		</section>
	</main>
	<footer>
		<p>&copy; 2021 Sales HTML Site</p>
	</footer>
</body>
</html>
```

4. CSS styling: Once you have added all your content, you can now style your website using CSS. You can add colors, fonts, layout, etc. to make your website look professional and appealing.

```
/* CSS code */
body {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  margin: 0;
}

header {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px;
}

nav ul {
  list-style-type: none;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
}

nav li {
  float: left;
}

nav li a {
  display: block;
  color: white;
  text-align: center;
  padding: 14px 16px;
  text-decoration: none;
}

nav li a:hover {
  background-color: #111;
}

main {
  margin: 20px 20px;
}

h2 {
  color: #333;
}

img {
  width: 200px;
  height: 200px;
  object-fit: cover;
}

section {
  margin-bottom: 40px;
}

form {
  width: 50%;
  margin-left: auto;
  margin-right: auto;
}

input[type=text], input[type=email], textarea {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 12px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 4px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  margin-top: 6px;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
  resize: vertical;
}

input[type=submit] {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  padding: 12px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

And that's it! You now have a basic sales HTML website. You can further enhance it with JavaScript and other advanced features.
